The Red Ants were brought in on Thursday morning to remove residents who built shacks on a piece of land in the area. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng motorists were urged to avoid the Moroka Bypass in Lenasia South where protests have broken out following evictions.The Red Ants were brought in on Thursday morning to remove residents who built shacks on a piece of land in the area.A Red Ants employee has died after being stabbed during the clashes, while two others are in critical condition in hospital.Gauteng traffic police spokesperson Obed Sibasa says shops have been looted and gunshots reported in the area. We are appealing to motorists and other road users to avoid the N12 water works near the two Sasol garages as roads are barricaded and the same goes for Impala Road as you head for Leratong Hospital. 